<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>POLICE AND CRIME COMMISSIONERS</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:16pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">Written evidence from </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">Frank A Chapman</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt"> [PCC Progress </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">47</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:16pt">]</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> I am a County Councillor and the Chairman of the Staffordshire and Stoke-on-Trent Police and Crime Panel.  The Panel consists of 12 members, 1 from the County Council, 1 from the City of Stoke-on-Trent, 8 from the each of the District Councils within the County and 2 Independent Members.  I am a retired police officer having served for over 30 years in 5 different police forces and I am </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a former member of the Police Authority.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Crime has diverse</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> causes and addressing these effectively must fall within the remit of many agencies.  Being </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">raised in a household where there</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is a history of gainful employment greatly lessens the prospect of falling into a life of crime. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Police and Crime Commissioners have been</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> elected by a small minority                  of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the population to address criminality over large areas.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">They we</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">re elected against a backdrop of a fall</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in the numbers of recorded crime.  There are large areas of crime that are under recorded and indeed the nature of crime may well be changing.  Domestic Violence, Cyber Crime and Shoplifting are all under recorded.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A Commissioner</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> success in reducing crime is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> dependent on the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> formulation of strategies that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">capture the imagination of agencies that can contribute towards successful outcomes.  Much depends on the skill of the individual and the abil</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ity to embrace Councils some of whom may</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be of a different political persuasion.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">   Existing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">crime and safety </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">partnership </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">governance structures do not reflect the role of the Police and Crime Commissioner.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Commissioners make crime and disorder reduction grants and must include the details of these grants in their Police and Crime Plans together with any conditions attached to the grants.  It is too early to evaluate the success of these interventions but they will depend on the grants being effectively targeted </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">at the areas where there is the greatest need and where they will achieve maximum impact.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Policing is not just about reducing crime.  It is about the protection of life and property and above all preserving the Queens Peace.  The Commissioner is charged with providing an efficient and effective police force for the area.  In this country we follow the principle laid down by Robert Peel of policing for the people by the people.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">For this to be achieved the service must </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">be seen as fully accountable and politically independent</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> if it is to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enjoy the confidence of all factions of the population.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commissioner</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">often </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">seen as</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> political appointees and their performance will be viewed as reflecting on their individual parties.  For </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">this reason they may not always</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> receive the degree of support across the whole of their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">area necessary</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to combat crime and secure confidence in the Police Service.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  They set out their goals</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in a Draft Police &amp; Crime Plan which is conside</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">red by the Police &amp; Crime Panel.  The Panel publishes its response </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to which the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commissioner must</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> due regard.  Unfortunately I have experienced a situation whereby this consultation process has been used by a Council to undermine the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commissioner’s standing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Police and Crime Panels are under resourced and frequently rely on the goodwill of the host authority in order to carry out their</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> function which includes support for the Commissioner.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  The extensive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">use of local authority</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> officers is needed to effectively scrutinise the Commissioner and this particularly applies in budget and precept setting.  Despite extensive publicity it has proved difficult to promote the role of the Panel but planned webcasting may help to overcome this.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Commissioner has considerable autonomy and the importance of the Panel in holding him to account between elections must not be understated.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Frank A Chapman</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">November 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>